Hide the in-game container/loot/pickpocket window AND the player inventory
window when Looting is in DS mode, so the companion (bottom-screen) looting UI is
the sole looting surface; show both native windows when Looting is Vanilla. Same
pattern as companion-hide-dialogue-on-hideui.patch.

Re-gated July 2026 from the global Hide UI flag (mHudEnabled) onto the per-element
DS flag companionDsLooting() (androidmain.cpp, pushed from Kotlin's
"game_ui_looting" GameUiMode). DS -> suppress the native windows; Vanilla -> show
them. Both gates live in updateVisible(), which runs at the tail of pushGuiMode/
popGuiMode, so the gate is applied the moment the container mode is entered.

Hunk 1 — container window. Gate = !companionDsLooting() && containsMode(GM_Container):
  * containsMode(GM_Container) is correct here (unlike the dialogue window's
    getMode()==GM_Dialogue, which dodges a pushed Barter/Spells/Travel service
    window): nothing is pushed on top of the container window during looting, and
    it matches the guard in ContainerWindow::onClose() (container.cpp), which
    early-returns while containsMode(GM_Container) is true. That guard is why
    hiding mid-loot is safe — onClose() does not resolve the pickpocket, drop
    over-encumbrance items, or reset the reference while the mode is still active.
  * The companion overlay detects open/close via the Lua UiModeChanged event
    (mode push/pop), NOT this window's visibility, so hiding it does not disturb
    COMPANION_CONTAINER_OPEN/_CLOSED.

Hunk 2 — player inventory window. GM_Container's GuiModeState shows BOTH the
container window and the inventory window, so hunk 1 alone leaves the inventory
window on the top screen. It must be hidden too, but ONLY during looting in DS
mode (never during normal inventory use, and not during Barter/Companion).

  Placement matters: a few lines below hunk 1, updateVisible() has
    mInventoryWindow->setVisible(getMode()==GM_Container || GM_Barter || GM_Companion);
  which UNCONDITIONALLY re-shows the inventory window for GM_Container. Putting
  the gate up next to the mContainerWindow line (as first drafted) is silently
  overridden by that later line. So the hide is applied immediately AFTER it,
  scoped to GM_Container:
    if (mInventoryWindow && companionDsLooting() && getMode() == GM_Container)
        mInventoryWindow->setVisible(false);
  Truth table: normal inventory (GM_Inventory, this else-if not entered) → shown;
  looting + Vanilla (companionDsLooting() false) → shown; looting + DS
  (companionDsLooting() true && GM_Container) → hidden. InventoryWindow::onOpen()
  re-adds the ItemTransfer target that onClose() removes, so switching Looting
  back to Vanilla during a loot restores native shift-click transfer — nothing breaks.

Hunk 3 — restore pickpocket detection while hidden (popGuiMode). Getting caught
pickpocketing is rolled in ContainerWindow::onClose() -> PickpocketItemModel::
onClose() (pickpocket.finish()). That runs via the mode-pop's
GuiModeState::update(false) -> WindowBase::setVisible(false), which fires onClose()
ONLY on a visible->hidden transition. Once hunk 1 has hidden the container window
(DS looting), the mode-pop's setVisible(false) is a no-op, so onClose() never
fires and pickpocketing is never detected (it works with the native window
visible, because then the pop is the visible->hidden transition).

This is the same class of bug as the COMPANION_DIALOGUE_CLOSED-when-hidden gotcha,
but it CANNOT be fixed in ContainerWindow::exit() the way the dialogue signal was:
popGuiMode(true) calls window->exit() BEFORE popping the mode, and BOTH
ContainerWindow::onClose() and PickpocketItemModel::onClose() early-return while
containsMode(GM_Container) is true — so the finish roll can only run POST-pop.
Instead, in popGuiMode, capture whether the container window was already hidden
BEFORE the pop, and after mGuiModeStates[mode].update(false) call
mContainerWindow->onClose() explicitly (containsMode(GM_Container) is now false, so
the guards pass). The !isVisible() gate prevents a double-roll: when the window was
visible, update(false) fires onClose() itself (and resetReference() nulls mModel);
when it was hidden, update(false) is a no-op and our explicit call is the only one.
Single roll either way, no change for the native-visible case, and it covers every
close path (Close / Take All / Dispose / B-Escape / Lua removeMode) since they all
funnel through popGuiMode. NOTE: this restores only the ON-CLOSE finish roll; the
per-take roll (PickpocketItemModel::stealItem) is still bypassed because companion
takes move items via Lua moveInto rather than the native item model.

--- a/apps/openmw/mwgui/windowmanagerimp.cpp
+++ b/apps/openmw/mwgui/windowmanagerimp.cpp
@@ -659,6 +659,15 @@
         // the stack, so hiding it mid-conversation does not end the dialogue or clear history.
         if (mDialogueWindow && getMode() == GM_Dialogue)
             mDialogueWindow->setVisible(!companionDsConversation() && !loading);
+
+        // COMPANION: hide the container/loot/pickpocket window when Looting is in DS mode so
+        // the companion (bottom) screen is the sole looting surface; show the native window
+        // when Looting is Vanilla (companionDsLooting() false). ContainerWindow::onClose()
+        // early-returns while containsMode(GM_Container) is true (see container.cpp), so
+        // hiding it mid-loot neither resolves the pickpocket nor drops items — the session
+        // ends normally only when the container mode is actually removed.
+        if (mContainerWindow)
+            mContainerWindow->setVisible(!companionDsLooting() && containsMode(GM_Container));

         bool gameMode = !isGuiMode();

@@ -711,6 +720,16 @@
             mHud->setDrowningBarVisible(false);
             mInventoryWindow->setVisible(
                 getMode() == GM_Container || getMode() == GM_Barter || getMode() == GM_Companion);
+            // COMPANION: also hide the player inventory window while looting in DS mode,
+            // so the top screen is fully clear (the companion bottom screen is the sole
+            // looting surface). This MUST come after the vanilla line above — that line
+            // unconditionally re-shows the inventory window for GM_Container, so gating it
+            // up by the mContainerWindow line would be overridden here. Scoped to
+            // GM_Container so normal inventory use and Barter/Companion are untouched;
+            // InventoryWindow::onOpen() re-adds the ItemTransfer target when Looting is set
+            // back to Vanilla, so nothing breaks.
+            if (mInventoryWindow && companionDsLooting() && getMode() == GM_Container)
+                mInventoryWindow->setVisible(false);
         }

         GuiMode mode = mGuiModes.back();
@@ -1501,8 +1520,21 @@
             mKeyboardNavigation->saveFocus(mode);
             if (containsMode(mode))
             {
+                // COMPANION: if the container window was already hidden by the DS-looting
+                // gate above, the update(false) below hides it via a no-op setVisible(false)
+                // that will NOT fire onClose() — so the pickpocket finish roll
+                // (ContainerWindow::onClose -> PickpocketItemModel::onClose) is skipped,
+                // and pickpocketing while hidden is never detected. Capture that here
+                // and run onClose() explicitly AFTER the pop, when containsMode(GM_Container)
+                // is false so the onClose guards pass. When the window was visible,
+                // update(false) fires onClose() itself (and resetReference() nulls mModel),
+                // so we must not double-run — hence the !isVisible() gate.
+                const bool containerHiddenOnPop
+                    = (mode == GM_Container && mContainerWindow && !mContainerWindow->isVisible());
                 mGuiModes.pop_back();
                 mGuiModeStates[mode].update(false);
+                if (containerHiddenOnPop)
+                    mContainerWindow->onClose();
                 MWBase::Environment::get().getLuaManager()->uiModeChanged(MWWorld::Ptr());
             }
         }
